Available Tools: create_volume | attach_volume | detach_volume | snapshot_volume | list_volumes
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "volume_id": "string", "instance_id": "string", "size_gb": number }
Response Schema: { "volume_id": "string", "size_gb": number, "state": "string", "attached_to": "string" }
---
Question: List all storage volumes currently available in the us-east-1 region to check for unattached resources.
Call: { "func_call": "list_volumes", "volume_id": "", "instance_id": "", "size_gb": 0 }
Response: { "volume_id": "vol-0a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8", "size_gb": 100, "state": "available", "attached_to": "" }

Question: I need to create a backup snapshot of the database volume vol-db-prod-01 before applying tonight's patches.
Call: { "func_call": "snapshot_volume", "volume_id": "vol-db-prod-01", "instance_id": "", "size_gb": 0 }
Response: { "volume_id": "vol-db-prod-01", "size_gb": 500, "state": "snapshotting", "attached_to": "i-0987654321abcdef0" }

Question: Show me the details of the newly created volume vol-new-archive to confirm its size and attachment status.
Call: { "func_call": "list_volumes", "volume_id": "vol-new-archive", "instance_id": "", "size_gb": 0 }
Response: { "volume_id": "vol-new-archive", "size_gb": 2000, "state": "available", "attached_to": "" }

